Package: bayesianssd
Type: Package
Title: Software for the automatic computation of sample sizes for a Bayesian analysis workflow
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Christoph Waterkamp & Jeannine Veseljak
Maintainer: Christoph Waterkamp <christoph.waterkamp@uni-due.de>
Description: This package helps you find the smallest sample size needed to reach a desired statistical power in an experiment. The experiment data are simulated using a Bayesian model. To make the process faster, the number of required simulations is approximated using a beta model. The software checks whether a sample size is sufficient by estimating power. Based on this, it suggests the next sample size to test using a simple approximation.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: rstan, ggplot2, doFuture, HDInterval, gridExtra
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0), rstanarm, knitr, rmarkdown
